The resource type in the XML resource files is shown as `&lt;string-array&gt;` and also the Xposed API documentation knowns the type `String Array`. However the documentation is not clear what concrete values are acceptable for `type`:

[`public void setReplacement (String pkg, String type, String name, Object replacement)`][1] 

&gt; type	The type name, e.g. string. See Resources.getResourceTypeName(int).

Tracing back the path through the AOSP sources what values can be returned by `Resources.getResourceTypeName(int)` and therefore are a valid resource type name you end up in the file [Resource.cpp](https://github.com/aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base/blob/e80b45506501815061b079dcb10bf87443bd385d/tools/aapt2/Resource.cpp#L47) and it&#39;s `StringPiece to_string(ResourceType type)` method. It contains all possible resource type names. At the moment therefore the following values are allowed:

    &quot;^attr-private&quot;
    &quot;anim&quot;
    &quot;animator&quot;
    &quot;array&quot;
    &quot;attr&quot;
    &quot;bool&quot;
    &quot;color&quot;
    &quot;configVarying&quot;
    &quot;dimen&quot;
    &quot;drawable&quot;
    &quot;font&quot;
    &quot;fraction&quot;
    &quot;id&quot;
    &quot;integer&quot;
    &quot;interpolator&quot;
    &quot;layout&quot;
    &quot;menu&quot;
    &quot;mipmap&quot;
    &quot;navigation&quot;
    &quot;plurals&quot;
    &quot;raw&quot;
    &quot;string&quot;
    &quot;style&quot;
    &quot;styleable&quot;
    &quot;transition&quot;
    &quot;xml&quot;

In your case you used `&quot;string-array&quot;` which would be consistent with the xml tag the resource was defined it. However as you can see this type is not a valid resource type name. The correct resource type therefore in your case is `&quot;array&quot;`.

